# Staging / New Environment Deploy Checklist

When deploying the backend to a new environment (Railway, staging, production), always verify these items BEFORE telling the user the deploy is done:

## Database

- [ ] **Seed data exists** — The cloud database starts empty. Confirm that `backend/app/seed.py` covers all required reference data (vendors, categories, etc.). If new seed data is needed, add it to `seed.py` — it runs automatically on startup.
- [ ] **Migrations ran** — Tables are created via `Base.metadata.create_all()` on startup. If using Alembic in the future, ensure migrations are applied.

## Environment Variables

- [ ] All required env vars are set on the hosting platform (not just in local `.env`)
- [ ] `FRONTEND_URL` is set to the actual frontend URL (for CORS)
- [ ] `DATABASE_URL` points to the cloud database (not localhost)
- [ ] API keys (RESEND_API_KEY, MPESA_* keys) are set if those features should work
- [ ] `ENVIRONMENT` is set to `staging` or `production` (not `development`)

## End-to-End Verification

After deploy, always smoke test:
- [ ] `GET /health` returns 200
- [ ] Sign up a test user
- [ ] Log in and get a token
- [ ] Hit authenticated endpoints (vendors, dashboard, user profile)
- [ ] Verify seed data is populated (vendors list is not empty)

## CI/CD Secrets

If GitHub Actions deploys are configured, verify these secrets exist:
- `RAILWAY_TOKEN`, `RAILWAY_PROJECT_ID`, `RAILWAY_SERVICE_ID`
- `VERCEL_TOKEN`, `VERCEL_ORG_ID`, `VERCEL_PROJECT_ID`, `STAGING_API_URL`
